Make the sweet potato fries: Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425
degrees. Cut the @sweet potatoes{2} into thin sticks, (like French fries). Toss
them on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} and a
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for about ~{25%minutes},
tossing once, until golden brown.

Prep the remaining ingredients: Mince the @garlic{4%cloves}(minced). Peel and
grate the @carrots{2}(peeled and grated) with a #box grater{}. Halve, peel, and
finely dice the @red onion{2}(peeled and finely diced). Place ½ cup diced onion
aside in a large #bowl{}.

Make the barbecue sauce: Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{}
over medium heat before adding the remaining onion. Cook, tossing, for
~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add the @chili powder{2%teaspoon} (start with 1
teaspoon and go up from there) and cook another ~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Add
the @BBQ sauce{4%ounce}, @white wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, and ½ cup
@water{1/2%cup} to the #pot{}. Reduce to a low simmer until ready to use.

Cook the burgers: Add the @ground pork{20%ounce} and garlic to the bowl with the
diced onion. Season generously with @salt{generous} and @pepper{generous} (we
used @kosher salt{1%teaspoon}). Form into 4 patties. Heat a large drizzle of
@olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the patties to the pan.
Cook ~{4-6%minutes} per side, until cooked through.

Make the coleslaw: While the burgers cook, combine the remaining
@white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{3%tablespoon}, and
@sugar{2%teaspoon} in a large bowl. Toss in the @shredded red cabbage{8%ounce}
and carrots. Season with salt and pepper.

Finish and plate: Split the @potato buns{4} and place in the oven to toast
~{2-3%minutes}. Spread each bun with barbecue sauce, top with a pork burger, and
finish with some of the coleslaw. Serve the sweet potato fries and remaining
coleslaw on the side. Use any extra barbecue sauce and mayonnaise for dipping
the fries. Enjoy!